===2020 census===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Pajaro Dunes had a population of 122. The population density was {{convert|47.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Pajaro Dunes was 71 (58.2%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 8 (6.6%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 37 (30.3%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 6 (4.9%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 46 persons (37.7%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Pajaro Dunes CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0655048 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 61 households, out of which 11 (18.0%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 28 (45.9%) were married-couple households, 3 (4.9%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 20 (32.8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 10 (16.4%) had a male householder with no partner present. 22 households (36.1%) were one person, and 17 (27.9%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.0.<ref name=DP1/> There were 35 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (57.4% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Pajaro Dunes CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0655048 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 15 people (12.3%) under the age of 18, 11 people (9.0%) aged 18 to 24, 36 people (29.5%) aged 25 to 44, 21 people (17.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 39 people (32.0%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 42.0{{nbsp}}years.    There were 65 males and 57 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 564 housing units at an average density of {{convert|220.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 61 (10.8%) were occupied. Of these, 58 (95.1%) were owner-occupied, and 3 (4.9%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

